title: Remaining PSL X matches moved to UAE: PCB - DAWN.COM
content:
The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has announced that the remaining eight fixtures of the Pakistan Super League (PSL) X have been moved to the United Arab Emirates.

“The PCB confirms that the remaining fixtures of the HBL PSL X have been shifted to the UAE,” said a press release on the PCB website. It added that the qualifier, both eliminators and the final will be played in the UAE.

It added that the following fixtures will be rescheduled:

“The exact schedule of matches, outlining the dates and venues, will be shared in due course,” the statement added.
